            "name": "Description",
            "html": "Smugglers sneak their ill-gotten gains past nosey port functionaries as well as naval inspections and blockades, and are typically stealthy rapscallions, marvelously gifted beguilers, and nimblefingered pickpockets."
        }
    ],
